Security Recommendations
1. Enable Multi-Factor Authentication

Provides an additional verification step beyond passwords.

2. Enforce Strong Password Policies

Reduces the likelihood of password-based attacks.

3. Perform Regular Software Updates

Removes known vulnerabilities before attackers exploit them.

4. Conduct Cybersecurity Awareness Programs

Educates users about common cyber threats.

5. Schedule Frequent Data Backups

Ensures quick recovery after data loss.

6. Deploy Antivirus Solutions

Detects and blocks malicious software.

7. Secure the Network with Firewalls

Prevents unauthorized network access.

8. Encrypt Confidential Data

Protects information even if it is stolen.

9. Apply Role-Based Access Control

Limits access according to user responsibilities.

10. Monitor Systems Continuously

Helps detect suspicious activities at an early stage.